\begin{aligned}\n&\frac{1}{2}, \frac{1}{4}, \frac{1}{2}, \frac{1}{2}, \frac{1}{3}, \quad \mathcal{F}(0)=\frac{4 x^{2}}{(2-2)^{3}} \frac{x^{0}}{x^{2}}\\\n&0=(x-2)^{3}\\\n&\sqrt{0}=(\sqrt{x-2})^{2}\\\n&\begin{array}{c}\n0=x_{i} \\\n+2\n\end{array}\\\n&x=2\n\end{aligned}[imath]0=x_{i} [/imath] [imath]+2[/imath]
